<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="occupied-adj">occupied <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'ɒkjupaɪd/    美 /'ɑːkjupaɪd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(地方) 被占领的；被侵占的</strong></h4>
<p>反 unoccupied </p>
<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[不用于名词前] 被占用的；有人使用的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Sorry, this seat is occupied.
抱歉，这个座位有人了。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[不用于名词前] 忙于...的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You can imagine how <strong>fully occupied</strong> I became, raising four boys under the age of 8!
你能想象我抚养四个不到八岁的小男孩会有多忙了吧！</p><footer>2011 天津</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>be occupied with (doing) sth / (in) doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I have been so occupied with work that I haven’t had time for social activities.
工作太忙，我一直没有时间参加社交活动。</p><footer>人教⑦ – 5</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He’s fully occupied looking after three small children.
照顾三个小孩把他忙得不可开交。</p></div></div>